clinic.name: Miranda Medical Centre & Skin Cancer Clinic
clinic.blurb:
Miranda Medical Centre has been a part of the Sutherland Shire Community for over 30 years, having operated since 1987. The centre has a proud history of providing reputable quality health services to all patients. It brings us great pleasure to now operate in outstanding new facilities, with innovative designs and the latest technology. 

Our new practice is a fully-accredited; purpose built premise. The centre currently has a team of 24 Full-time General Practitioners, along with a comprehensive range of Allied Health, on-site specialists and collection facilities.

Appointments are not necessary to see our General Practitioners as we accept walk-in patients at all times during our opening hours. For patients who have physically attended our practice in the past 12 months we are also able to offer bulk-billed telephone consults. Please phone the practice on 9540 1044.

We do however take appointments for our Skin Cancer Clinic. Appointments with our experienced Skin Cancer Doctors can be made here. Our Doctors have a special interest in Skin Cancer Checks, Diagnosis, Management and Surgical Options. 

Online Appointments will also be made with our Nurses when the Covid Vaccine is available.
